        <div class="category-brand--admin-blue block block-block-content block-block-content3c0390d2-e42c-4fb2-b432-eff4d823f143 panel o-box" id="block-ucpath">
         <h2 class="panel__title">
          UCPath
         </h2>
         <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item">
          <p>
           When UCPath launches at UC Davis on April 1st, it will bring some changes to the payroll process. Regular paychecks will no longer be picked up locally. All paychecks will be mailed on payday from a centralized service center in Arizona to the home address on file. Employees who are not enrolled in direct deposit should expect a delay when receiving their paycheck, every pay period.
          </p>
          <p>
           Employees are encouraged to sign up for direct deposit to avoid delays in getting paid. To sign up, you will need an active campus computing account (UCD login ID and Kerberos passphrase) and enroll via AYSO:
           <span>
            <span>
             <span>
              <a href="https://atyourserviceonline.ucop.edu/ayso/">
               https://atyourserviceonline.ucop.edu/ayso/
              </a>
              . If you have questions or need assistance enrolling, contact the Shared Services Organization at (530) 754-4772.
             </span>
            </span>
           </span>
          </p>
         </div>
